ic errors and are likely\nto be accurate. However, care must be taken to avoid the effects of\nconfirmation bias, which may be affecting recent measurements of dark energy\nparameters. For example, of the 28 measurements of Omega_Lambda in our sample\npublished since 2003, only 2 are more than 1 sigma from the WMAP results. Wider\nuse of blind analyses in cosmology could help to avoid this.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Dec 2011 03:32:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2015 15:29:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-22"}
